Professor Salim Abdool Karim has become a household name in the country amid the Covid-19 outbreak. The Infectious Disease specialist chairs government's advisory committee on coronavirus. He's also Director at the Centre for the AIDS Programme of Research in South Africa. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Professor Salim Abdool Karim says the easing lockdown regulations and the reopening schools are inevitable. He says normal life must be allowed to continue amid the coronavirus, as the virus is expected to be around for a while. WATCH: Professor Karim's full presentation Professor Karim chairs the government's advisory committee on coronavirus. Basic Education has proposed that pupils return to school in phases. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.